%U A397793 26672369184,92538198727,321055635752,1113883173392,3864550148744,13407823079930,46517630531716,161390104750683
%N A397793 Number of ways to tile a 2 X n strip with both bottom corners missing, using squares, dominoes, and Z-shaped tetrominoes.
%C A397793 Compare to A397583 which counts these tilings for a 2 X n strip with only one missing corner, and with T-shaped tetrominoes instead of Z-shaped tetrominoes. Also, compare to A397792 which counts these tilings for a 2 X n strip with alternate corners missing.
%H A397793 <a href="/index/Rec#order_06">Index entries for linear recurrences with constant coefficients</a>, signature (2,6,-2,-4,0,1).
%F A397793 a(n) = 2*a(n-1) + 6*a(n-2) - 2*a(n-3) - 4*a(n-4) + a(n-6).
%F A397793 G.f.: x^2*(-2 + x^2)/((-1 - x + x^2)*(1 - 3*x - 2*x^2 + x^3 + x^4)).
%F A397793 a(2*n) = b(n)^2 + c(n)^2 + a(n)^2 + c(n-1)^2 + 2*(b(n)*a(n-1) + b(n-1)*a(n)) for b(n) = A397792(n) and c(n) = A397583(n).
%e A397793 Here is one of the a(6)=214 ways to tile this 2 X 6 strip (with missing bottom corners) using squares, dominoes, and Z-shaped tetrominoes:
%e A397793    ___________
%e A397793   |_  |_|_|___|
%e A397793     |___|___|.
%t A397793 LinearRecurrence[{2, 6, -2, -4, 0, 1}, {2, 4, 19, 58, 214, 722}, 30]
%Y A397793 Cf. A397583, A397792.
%K A397793 nonn,easy,new
%O A397793 2,1
